    "possibleUpdate": false,
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n      <strong>Psionic Discipline:</strong>&nbsp;psychometabolism&nbsp;(str);\n    <br>\n    <strong>Level:</strong>&nbsp;Psion 7;\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    <br>\n    \n    <strong>Power Display:</strong>&nbsp;Vi (see text)\n<br>\n      <strong>Manifesting Time:</strong>&nbsp;1 round<br>\n    <strong>Range:</strong>&nbsp;medium (100 ft. + 10 ft./level)<br>\n    \n    <strong>Target:</strong>&nbsp;you and one object or creature\n<br>\n    \n    <strong>Duration:</strong>&nbsp;10 minutes/level or until discharged\n<br>\n    <strong>Power Points/Spell Points Cost:</strong>&nbsp;13<br>\n        <strong>Saving Throw:</strong>&nbsp;none\n        <br>\n        <strong>Power Resistance:</strong>&nbsp;no<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  \n\n<p>The manifester's body assimilates and converts energy attacks to a ray. The character gains resistance 10 to a specific energy attack. Once the power has prevented a total of 10 points of damage per manifester level (maximum 150 points) from specified energy attacks, it is discharged. Specified energy attacks include powers and spells that deal acid, cold, electricity, fire, and sonic damage. The character can discharge stored energy in a ray as a single ranged touch attack. This is a standard action. The ray is composed of the energy type absorbed. The character can choose to fire the ray prior to complete saturation of the energy barrier, though this ends the power. If the ray successfully strikes the target, the target takes a number of hit points equal to the total number of hit points successfully ignored by the energy barrier.\n</p>\n<hr/>\n\n\n\n\n\n</div>\n",
